                <h3> Wildfires Burning! <strike>Happy 4th of July!</strike></h3>
                    <p>
                    So far this summer has been HOT! <span class="update--label update--label-color-orange">Sat, 17 Jul 2   021</span><span class="update--color-orange">And the wildfires have been popping up all around us, but the closest one, the <a target="_new" href="https://www.kolotv.com/2021/07/16/tamarack-fire-burning-south-markleeville/">Tamarack Fire</a> has burned almost 21,000 acres with no containment and making the air quality pretty ugly and unhealthy (AQI of 175).</span> Back on the 4th, we headed up to the old mining town of Virginia City, Nevada for the parade. It was my first time to this parade and always find this small, historic town charming and fun. Grabbed a beer at Virginia City Brewing and watched the parade from the street. I took a few pictures which you can see here in my <a target="_new" href="https://jmgalleries.com/fieldnotes/independence-day-parade-in-virginia-city-nevada">fieldnotes filmstrip</a>. <span class="update--label update--label-color-green">Sun, 18 Jul 2021 </span> <span class="update--color-green">Also, been creating a lot of new youtube videos, so if you haven't seen any, go check them out <a target="_new" href="//vlog.jmgalleries.com">on my youtube channel</a>.</span>
                    </p>
                    
                <h3>Home Projects</h3>
                    <p>
                    Despite the temps creeping at the 100 mark and sometimes tipping over, we finally started our backyard patio. I must have rearranged a hundred or so pavers (2/3 times) like I was playing Tetris as we played with pattern ideas. We figured it out and now it's time to put in the work. And, hopefully we will get a few weeks to enjoy it before winter. <span class="update--label update--label-color-purple">Thu, 29 Jul 2021 </span> <span class="update--color-purple">The smoke from the Tamarack and Dixie fires have unfortunately slowed progress on the backyard paver project. Hopefully the air quality will improve as fire crews contain the disaster.</span>
                    </p>
                    
                    
                <h3>What's Cooking ... on the Traeger</h3>
                    <p>
                    It feels like eons ago was the last time I fired up "The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel" (that's our Traeger name). This past month has just been too hot to BBQ. Plus, we recently started using Home Chef and have made some really amazing meals with that subscription. But, I'm starting feel a craving for some tri-tip and beef ribs. Maybe some fresh coleslaw too. 
                    <br /><br />
                    Last smoke:<br /><a target="_new" href="https://www.traegergrills.com/recipes/beer-can-chicken">Roasted Beer Can Chicken</a> with <a target="_new" href="https://www.traegergrills.com/recipes/salted-baked-potatoes"> Salt Crusted Baked Potatoes</a>.
                    </p>
                    
                <h3>Photography</h3>
                    <p>
                    On the first day of the month I got a call wondering if I had the time to shoot a wedding ... on the same day. I rearranged a few things on the schedule, tossed together some gear and by lunch time I was heading to Genoa. It felt great to get back behind the camera in a way where I wasn't shooting clouds, water or trees and also interacting with people; real people, not people in a Zoom call. I could actually shake their hands and have a human connection. You can check out some of the wedding highlights on <a target="_new" href="https://jmgalleries.pixieset.com/angela-jonathan/">my portfolio site</a>.
                    <br /><br />
                    I also switched sending the once-a-month new release email to the First Friday of each month. Small change, but I think attaching it to a more popular event title will make it more attractive to look forward to. You can read the <a target="_new" href="https://mailchi.mp/ff463effb3c8/052021-nr-7072154">July First Friday New Release email</a> and <a target="_new" href="https://jmgalleries.com/signup">subscribe</a> so you don't want to miss August.
                    <br /><br />
                    <span class="update--label update--label-color-purple">Thu, 29 Jul 2021 </span> <span class="update--color-purple">This week I kicked off a new playlist on my YouTube channel called "Thoughts While Drinking Coffee...". They are short, 3 minutes or less, videos of me talking about photography things. <a target="_new" href="https://vlog.jmgalleries.com">Check it out</a>.</span>
                    </p>
                    
                <h3>Reading ...</h3>
                    <p>
