                <h3>What's on the television ...</h3>
                    <p>
                    I have been watching the new Marvel series, Loki. It's good. Both entertaining and a little thought provoking in terms of the MCU. As of today, however, there is still one more episode left and am excited about it. As far as movies go I finally watched Disney's Cruella. I liked it; not loved it. I hope they don't make a sequel. In the prime-time network world who isn't watching Holey Moley Season 3? If you haven't seen this fun, funny and crazy ultimate miniature golf game show then I strongly encourage you to look it up on Hulu and start. Oh, and Lego Masters too (Season 2). And, of course the filler shows being Moonshiners, American Ninja Warrior, Insane Pools, Bahamas Life and The American Barbecue ShowDown.
