                <h3>Thinking about fine-art ...</h3>
                    <p>
                    I'm not really a fan or believer of the  mantra, "Go Big or Go Home", within the fine-art community. Maybe it's because I don't have a home or office that can accommodate super-large imagery or that I don't have a medium format camera which would more easily allow me to create larger-than-life images. This is why I tend to keep my fine-art in the medium (16x24) to large (24x36) size and leave the ginormous to photographers who have the space and gear. With that said, I have been working on bringing some new ideas to the art-collection community which I hope to start showing-off by the end of year ... somewhere, most likely Reno/Tahoe area. 
                    <br /><br />
